Problem statement
The Information Security organization operates as a collection of siloed domain teams — each with its own tools, processes, and SLA definitions — forcing customers to lose critical time identifying the right teams, engaging them independently, and manually coordinating across domains, while leadership operates without unified visibility to manage risk, performance, and outcomes.


Solution description:

We will design and deploy an AI-powered IS Intake Agent — a single, intelligent front door where customers submit any security request via natural language chat or guided forms, and the agent automatically classifies, routes, and orchestrates fulfillment across all relevant security domain agents.
The platform delivers real-time request transparency to customers and a consolidated operational dashboard to leadership — transforming IS service delivery from a fragmented, manual process into a unified, accountable, and intelligent service experience.
